Tomcat
------

http://tomcat.apache.org/

$TOMCAT_HOME refers to the directory of a given version of tomcatâ€™s topmost directory.

We ran experiments using the test suites provided with the source code distributions of tomcat versions 7.0.53 and 8.0.5. We used Java 1.7.0_51 and Ant 1.9.3 for both tomcat versions. The following updates need to be made before running ant (See the BUILDING.txt for more setup instructions): 

	* tomcat-7.0.53
	
	  1. Add the following to build.xml: 
	     <!-- Using Java 7: Do not build dbcp -->
	     <property name="no.build.dbcp" value="true"/>

	  2. Set the following in build.properties.default
	     # Location of Java7 JDK

	  3. Set the following in build.properties.default
	     # ----- Default Base Path for Dependent Packages -----


	* tomcat-8.0.5
	
	  1. Set the following in build.properties.default
	     # ----- Default Base Path for Dependent Packages -----


Kamino
------

$KAMINO_HOME refers to the base directory of the Kamino project

1. Update TOMCAT_VERSION in src/edu/columbia/cs/psl/kamino/Constants.java to reflect the version of Tomcat to use (TOMCAT_8 or TOMCAT_7)

2. Compile and run src/edu/columbia/cs/psl/kamino/Instrumenter.java

	* TOMCAT_8
	  Command line arguments:
	  args[0] = $TOMCAT_HOME/apache-tomcat-8.0.5-src
	  args[1] = inst/tomcat-8.0.5

	* TOMCAT_7
	  Command line arguments:
	  args[0] = $TOMCAT_HOME/apache-tomcat-7.0.53-src
	  args[1] = inst/tomcat-7.0.53

3. Export Kamino project to $KAMINO_HOME/kamino.jar

4. From $KAMINO_HOME/inst/TOMCAT_VERSION run:
   > ant -lib ../../kamino.jar test


